# PR Create

When asked to create a pull request, follow these steps.

## 1. Verify Branch State

Ensure the working tree is clean — commit any uncommitted changes with a conventional commit message. If on main/master, create a feature branch first.

Use naming convention: `feat/PROJ-123-short-description`.

## 2. Push the Branch

Push with `git push -u origin HEAD` to set upstream tracking.

## 3. Generate PR Metadata

- **Title**: Derive from commit messages using conventional format (e.g., `feat: add user authentication`).
- **Body**: Include summary of changes, modified files, and test plan.
- Link Jira ticket in the PR description.

## 4. Create the PR

Show a preview of the PR to the user and ask for confirmation before creating.
Create as a draft PR using `gh pr create --draft`.

## 5. Post-Creation

Report the PR URL. Suggest running a PR review as a self-check.
